The paper deals with blind deconvolution, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. The use of sparse representations and random subspaces suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SP (Signal Processing). The mention of convex relaxation and nuclear-norm minimization suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Mathematical Methods). Finally, the application of the results to multipath channel estimation in wireless communications suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.SI (Systems and Control).
